%N A129655 Numbers that set a new record for number of Fibonacci divisors.
%C A129655 From a(1) up to a(14), last known term, this sequence is equivalent to: a(n) is the smallest number that has exactly n Fibonacci divisors (A000045). The products of the new Fibonacci divisors that appear successively are in A349100. - _Bernard Schott_, Jul 15 2022
%D A129655 J. Earls, Red Zen, Lulu Press, NY, 2006, p. 105.
%H A129655 David A. Corneth, <a href="/A129655/a129655_1.gp.txt">Some actual values and some upper bounds on a(n), for n=1..134</a>
%H A129655 David A. Corneth, <a href="/A129655/a129655_2.gp.txt">PARI program</a>
%F A129655 a(n) <= A035105(n+1). - _Daniel Suteu_, Sep 27 2019
%e A129655 5040 has 60 divisors with 7 of them being Fibonacci numbers, namely 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 21 and 144.
%Y A129655 Cf. A000045, A005086, A035105, A349100.
